<https://data.colonialcollections.nl/.well-known/genid/c4fa161041204dd6afad54eb2cf2fe8d> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "PUB EN\nEmilie van Kerckhoff traveled in the first half of the 20th century to North Africa, India, Japan and the Dutch East Indies. What she saw in the streets, in temples and palaces, she captured in her sketchbooks with pencil drawings and water colors. Together with Sara Swart, Van Kerckhoff made her first trip to Java in 1910. At the Borobudur and the Kratons of Yogyakarta and Solo, she focused on a multitude of new shapes and colors." .
